localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Transitions
localizedMetadata.description: Expand your leadership skills to achieve better business results through people and teams as you transition to new leadership roles.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Foundations
localizedMetadata.description: Learn the foundational principles of the leadership role, from strategic business planning and implementation through managing teams and people.

localizedMetadata.title: Women in Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Women leaders face unique challenges and opportunities. Learn how to lead effectively as a woman in today's workplace.

localizedMetadata.title: Cross-Cultural Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Today's leaders operate in a multi-cultural environment. Learn how to lead global teams to foster cross-cultural understanding.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership is Poetry
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership is a complex, long-studied part of human history.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership is a Marathon
localizedMetadata.description: We tend to focus on observable leadership behaviors rather than on what’s going on inside.  Management is a sprint; but leadership is a marathon.  Leaders create the future; they must run every day.  Be like a golfer; calm yourself; get your head in the game.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership and Power
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership is about power.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership is a Mindset
localizedMetadata.description: Many people ask whether leaders are born or made. Typically the focus is on the skill set a leader has. But John Foster illustrates that leadership is not so much about a skill set as it is a mindset.

localizedMetadata.title: Centered Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Centered leadership is five capabilities. Starting with yourself: 1) build on strengths; 2) frame and reframe (treat situations as learning opportunities; not things to fear); 3) create trust-based relationships; 4) take risks and own the results; and 5) infuse positive energy.

localizedMetadata.title: Women in Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Women in leadership, whether on the board or as CEOs, make businesses and the world better.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Women in Leadership

localizedMetadata.title: The Case for Influential Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership is about outputs; but leaders can’t create those outputs by themselves.  That means leadership is about people. Leaders need to motivate; encourage; and engage others; both in and outside their organization.  In short; leaders need to be able to influence others.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Defined
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership is of critical importance to business executives. Vishen Lakhiani defines his vision of great leadership; and how that vision changed over the years as he gained experience in the business world.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership in a Digital Space
localizedMetadata.description: If you have good leadership skills in general, leading in a digital space can open up new channels for your abilities.

parent.title: Leadership Insights on Leading in the Digital Era

localizedMetadata.title: Women & Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Women leaders face unique challenges and opportunities. Learn how to lead effectively as a woman in today's workplace.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Networking
localizedMetadata.description: Having a vibrant network is key to any leader's success. Identify ways to expand and reinforce your professional relationships.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Presence
localizedMetadata.description: Because leaders are people, too, they can react in the moment, briefly forgetting their professional role. These tips make it easier to maintain and sustain leadership presence.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: The Case for Influential Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership is about outputs, but leaders can’t create those outputs by themselves. That means leadership is about people. Leaders need to motivate, encourage, and engage others, both in and outside their organization. In short, leaders need to be able to influence others.

parent.title: Leadership Insights on Influence and Persuasion

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Is in the Trenches
localizedMetadata.description: Leaders are the ones willing to ask the questions. They are willing to be vulnerable; admit they don’t have the answers and ask the team; “What do you think?” The people on the front lines; in the trenches; have the answers.  Ask them.

localizedMetadata.title: Collaborative Leadership
localizedMetadata.description:
Collaborative leadership means 1) 
identifying important partners 
through a broad network; 2) 
modeling collaboration for team 
members; and 3) knowing when to 
stop collaborating. Collaborate 
with different people to innovate 
and get out of the daily routine.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership & Empathy
localizedMetadata.description: You are not a leader if no one is following.

localizedMetadata.title: Develop Your Leadership Signature
localizedMetadata.description: Every leader has a unique leadership signature; made up of a credo—their core values and beliefs; what gives them the confidence to lead; and what provides credibility with others. Deborah Ancona describes methods for identifying your credo; confidence; and credibility.

localizedMetadata.title: Slow Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Moving forward quickly on decisions often produces a better outcome when leaders take it slow.

parent.title: Leadership Insights on Leading with Agility

localizedMetadata.title: Communication is Key to Successful Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership requires courage and confidence because sometimes you’re unpopular.

localizedMetadata.title: The 5 Levels of Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Based on the 5 Levels of Leadership paradigm in his book, Developing the Leader Within You, and then expanded further in the book, The 5 Levels of Leadership, John will explain how leaders can understand and increase their effectiveness. To lead well, you must embrace your need for continual improvement, and the 5 Levels provide a leadership GPS to help you with your journey. You must know where you are, to know where you’re going.

localizedMetadata.title: The Dark Side of Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Leadership has a dark side; a "leadership shadow" that often creates an unknown; lurking fear.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: Situational Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Situational leaders tailor their approach to the situation. Styles range from autocratic to participative; from push (fact based) to pull (listening and asking question); from analytic to relational. Practice different styles in venues that are outside your usual domain.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Leading with Vision

localizedMetadata.title: EQ and Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Everything in business is gray; good leaders see all sides; they have high EQ. For example; a great negotiation is one where everyone wins. Try to see things from the perspective of employees; customers; and shareholders. We’re all in it together. Try to work it out.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Leading with Emotional Intelligence

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Is About Convening
localizedMetadata.description: The skill set that effective leaders possess today is complex and varied—but one of the most important skills a leader has is the ability to bring diverse people together and tap into their collective wisdom; explains Larry Dressler.

localizedMetadata.title: Do-It-Yourself Leadership Development
localizedMetadata.description: In these challenging economic times; the concept of do-it-yourself leadership development as proposed by Andrew Simon’s company is a highly appropriate solution for the task of training an organization’s future managers.

localizedMetadata.title: Do-It-Yourself Leadership Development
localizedMetadata.description: In these challenging economic times; the concept of do-it-yourself leadership development as proposed by Andrew Simon’s company is a highly appropriate solution for the task of training an organization’s future managers.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: Customer First Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Customer satisfaction is crucial to business success. Learn how to lead with customers at the forefront of the business.

localizedMetadata.title: Learning Is the Foundation of Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Knowing is about the past. Learning is about creating the success of your people; your organization; and yourself. Learning is the foundation of leadership.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership in the Digital Era
localizedMetadata.description: In this keynote, Charlene Li draws from her expertise to look at, how organizations manage digital transformations, the leadership required to manage change, and the culture necessary to execute on growth strategies. You’ll learn the art and science of how to listen, share, and engage with your employees and customers in the digital era. She’ll also discuss common objections and concerns among leaders—and how to overcome them.

localizedMetadata.title: Women in Leadership: Adapt Your Style to Avoid Pigeonholing
localizedMetadata.description: To avoid being pigeonholed, women in leadership need to vary their leadership styles.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Women in Leadership

localizedMetadata.title: What Is Ethical Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: The seven lenses of ethical responsibility are profits; laws; character; people; communities; the planet; and the greater good.  All seven perspectives are important in order to live ethically in a global society.

localizedMetadata.title: Inspiration is Foundational to Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Inspiration is allowing people to be validated for their worth. Inspiration is sharing a vision of what we do; why we do it; where we’re going; and how their role fits that value proposition; no matter what they do. Inspiration is telling people that what they do matters.

localizedMetadata.title: Develop your Leadership Signature
localizedMetadata.description: Every leader has a unique leadership signature, made up of a credo—their core values and beliefs; what gives them the confidence to lead; and what provides credibility with others. Deborah Ancona describes methods for identifying your credo, confidence, and credibility.

parent.title: Leadership Insights on Leading with Executive Presence
Building Career Development Programs and Succession Planning

localizedMetadata.title: Four Aspects of Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: 1) Be yourself. It takes too much effort to be someone else. 2) Surround yourself with people who are good at things you are bad at. 3) Everyone wants to perform and is only waiting to be inspired. 4) Go beyond logic and reason to do impossible things.

localizedMetadata.title: Define The Purpose Of Your Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: True and lasting leadership derives from intrinsic motivations. William George shares a touching story about how never to lose one's sense of purpose.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership in the Digital Era
localizedMetadata.description: As companies tackle the transformation brought about by the digital era, leaders must embrace new technologies while guiding their teams through a rapidly changing future.

parent.title: Leadership Insights on Leading in the Digital Era

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Lessons
localizedMetadata.description: Smart leaders know how to coach through mistakes.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Developing as a Leader

localizedMetadata.title: The 3 Ps of Leadership: People, Purpose, and Performance
localizedMetadata.description: The leadership model starts with meaningful work for the people entrusted to you. Then; to inspire the people you must give them a purpose. Finally; you’ve got to perform — create value for all stakeholders. You need all three: people; purpose; and performance.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Leading with Vision

localizedMetadata.title: Agile Leadership
localizedMetadata.description: Leaders should try to create an organization that is agile, flexible, and resilient.

parent.title: Leadership Insights on Leading with Agility

localizedMetadata.title: Preparing for a Leadership Development Plan
Leadership Is About Behavior
localizedMetadata.description: We judge ourselves by our intentions but we judge others by their behavior.  Others judge us by our behavior; not our intentions.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Vision
localizedMetadata.description: Being an authentic leader means envisioning your legacy and taking action now to realize tomorrow's dreams.

localizedMetadata.title: Leadership Tips for New Managers
localizedMetadata.description: Linda Hill offers several suggestions for new managers.

parent.title: Expert Insights on Being a First-time Manager
